<TITLE> Khaleda 'barred from honouring martyrs timely' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, 21 Feb (bdnews24.com)  Leader of the opposition and BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia was not allowed to pay homage to the language martyrs alongside VIPs at the Central Shaheed Minar after zero hour of the Ekushey February, her press secretary Maruf Kamal Khan alleged. He said police intercepted her motorcade at Abdul Gani Road at 11:45 pm and again near Doel Chattar at 12:00 midnight when she was moving towards the Shaheed Minar, or martyr monument, to place wreaths. "You cannot go to the Shaheed Minar now. You can go only when the president and the prime minister leave there," Maruf quoted an unnamed police officer as telling the leaders accompanying Khaleda. He said: "Cabinet members, deputy speaker, diplomats, chiefs of the three services and leaders pro-Awami League organizations placed wreaths after the president and the prime minister. But the opposition leader was not allowed." "The government has not showed her the due honour... It's indecorous, he added. Maruf said police allowed Khaleda and the leaders accompanying her after 12:12 am when the president and the prime minister left the venue. She later placed wreaths at the Shaheed Minar amid serious insecurity, 
